      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That sounds like a very one-sided way to look at it. You're basically saying the only \"real solution\" is free market stuff. But what about the workers in industries like steel or manufacturing who lose their livelihoods because of cheap imports? Isn't it a bit unfair to say tariffs are just a \"tax\" while ignoring the fact that they can save local jobs and national security?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
